# Keep the repository normalized to LF on every platform. Go, shell, and
# markdown all tolerate LF on Windows, and a synced-across-workstations project
# benefits from deterministic line endings regardless of each PC's autocrlf.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows launchers must be CRLF if ever committed (the daemon generates the
# .vbs launcher at runtime, so none are tracked today — this is a guardrail).
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.vbs text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf

# Binary assets: never normalize.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.gz binary
*.zip binary
